x10.matrix.sparse

Class Compress2D

  • x10.matrix.sparse.Compress2D

  • public class Compress2D
    This class provides abstraction of 2-dimension compressed array based on array of 1-dimensional compress array.

        operator()=
        

        public void operator()=(x10.lang.Int i,
               x10.util.Pair<x10.lang.Int,x10.lang.Double> w)
        

        Set (surface index, value) pair in the i-th compressed line.
The data entry of surface index must exist, otherwise the operation
fails.
This operator should be used with caution.
Modifying compressed data after it is created should be avoided.

        copy
        

        public static x10.lang.Int copy(Compress2D srcC2D,
                x10.lang.Int srcLineOffset,
                Compress2D dstC2D,
                x10.lang.Int dstLineOffset,
                x10.lang.Int lineCnt)
        

        Copy the specified range of compress lines from source to target.
All compressed lines (offset-length) shoudl not be referenced, untill they are reset.
The range of compressed lines' offsets are adjusted based on the count of compressed array.
        

        Parameters:
        srcC2D - the source compress 2D array
        srcLineOffset - the starting line int 2D array
        dstC2D - the target compress 2D array
        dstLineOffset - line offset of destination compressed 2D
        lineCnt - number of lines to be copied
        

        Returns:
        number of compressed elements copied

        serializeIndex
        

        public x10.lang.Int serializeIndex(x10.lang.Int ldm,
                          x10.lang.Int lineOff,
                          x10.lang.Int lineCnt)
        

        The storage of compress array does not indicate the start of each compress line
in Compress2D. The offset and length of a compress line are recorded in compress1D feilds.
To reduce communication data, compress1D fields are not transfered with compress array.


         This function is used to mark the start offset of compress lines in their
storage (CompressArray), so that the offset values can be rebuilt.
The mechanism is to set the index value at the start of a compress line to negative.
        

        Parameters:
        ldm - -- Size of the origianl (uncompressed) line in 2D, which is also the leading dimension of matrix.
        lineOff - -- offset line of the starting compressed line
        lineCnt - -- Number of compressed lines
        

        Returns:
        -- storage size for the range of compress lines
